        "inputAnchors": [],
        "inputs": {
          "template": "You are SCM Assistant.\n\nAnswer the user using the following information.\n\nQuestion:\n{input}\n\nInformation:\n\nQ1. Which Tier-3 suppliers have an active disruption flag, and what response level applies per policy?\n\nAnswer:\n11 Tier-3 suppliers: Dravex Components India, Plataforma Metales SA, Maghreb Castworks, Helios Pack Greece, Cerromax Mineria, Orinoco Pack SAPI, Quetzal Textiles, Sibertek Molding, Archipelago PCB Corp, Varna Electronics EAD, Deltaforge Vietnam.\n\nAll are High Risk with an active flag → Level 3 Activate per Policy §9 requiring CPO escalation and alternate supplier activation at minimum 40% volume.\n\nQ2. Which suppliers qualify for the annual Volume Rebate Program and how many are there?\n\nAnswer:\n19 suppliers qualify.\n\nCriteria:\nTier-1 + OTD ≥ 93%\nDefect < 0.5%\nSustainability Score ≥ 85\n\nQ3. Which region has the highest total PO value and does it breach the concentration limit?\n\nAnswer:\nEMEA at $193,987,179.91.\n\nApproximately 48.5% of total spend.\n\nThis breaches the 45% concentration cap.\n\nQ4. Which suppliers are on Supplier Watch List status and what does it restrict?\n\nAnswer:\n11 suppliers are on Supplier Watch List.\n\nSWL restricts new PO issuance to 20% of prior quarter volume.\n\nQ5. Which product category has the highest average defect rate and does it exceed the Tier-2 limit?\n\nAnswer:\nMechanical Components.\n\nAverage defect rate: 2.12%.\n\nBelow the Tier-2 limit of 2.50%.",
